<h1>MapLegend</h1>
<p>An interactive, toggleable legend control that wires layer visibility groups to a customizable item template.</p>

<h2 id="overview">// overview</h2>
<p>Configure legend content directly on <code>LegendMapControl</code> inside <code>SgbMap.Controls</code>. This control-driven contract renders a collapsible panel whose items map to layer visibility groups on the map.</p>
<p><code>MapLegend</code> is now a legacy migration component and throws at runtime. This is an intentional breaking change in Phase 1 so consumers move to <code>LegendMapControl.Content</code>.</p>

<h2 id="definition">// definition</h2>
<p>Build a <code>MapLegendDefinition</code> to describe the legend structure. Each section contains items with an id, label, optional description, and a list of layer IDs to control.</p>

<CodeBlock Language="csharp" Files="@(new Dictionary<string, string>
{
    ["Legend definition"] =
@"var legend = new MapLegendDefinition(
    Sections:
    [
        new MapLegendSectionDefinition(
            ""Infrastructure"",
            [
                new MapLegendItemDefinition(
                    ""stations"",
                    ""Stations"",
                    ""Railway stations"",
                    [new MapLegendTargetDefinition(""base-style"", [""stations-circle"", ""stations-label""])],
                    IsVisibleByDefault: true,
                    IsToggleable: true
                ),
                new MapLegendItemDefinition(
                    ""tracks"",
                    ""Tracks"",
                    Targets: [new MapLegendTargetDefinition(""base-style"", [""tracks-line""])],
                    IsVisibleByDefault: true,
                    IsToggleable: true
                ),
            ]
        ),
    ]);",
})" />

<h2 id="control_options">// control_options</h2>
<p><code>LegendMapControl</code> now carries placement, chrome, and content in constructor-complete grouped options.</p>

<CodeBlock Language="csharp" Files="@(new Dictionary<string, string>
{
    ["Control options"] =
@"var controls = new List<MapControl>
{
    new LegendMapControl(
        ""overlay-legend"",
        new MapControlPlacement(ControlPosition.TopRight, 500, Enabled: true),
        new LegendChromeOptions(""Legend"", Collapsible: true, InitiallyOpen: true, ClassName: null),
        new LegendContentOptions(legend, ItemTemplate: null, OnItemVisibilityChanged: default)
    ),
};

<SgbMap Controls=""@controls"" />",
})" />

<h2 id="custom_templates">// custom_templates</h2>
<p>Use the <code>ItemTemplate</code> render fragment to fully customize how each legend item appears. The template context provides the item definition, current visibility state, and a callback to toggle visibility.</p>

<p>See the <a href="components/tracked-data-source">tracked data layers train tracking example</a> for a full implementation with custom SVG swatch artwork and checkbox badges.</p>
